   Here is the 54-46 roll call by which the
Senate voted early Friday to approve a deficit-reduction passage.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to pass the bill and a
``no'' vote was a vote to defeat it.
   Voting ``yes'' were 31 Democrats and 23 Republicans.
   Voting ''no'' were 24 Democrats and 22 Republicans.
