   Here is the the 58-39 roll call by which the
Senate voted to reject administration-backed provisions on aid to
El Salvador.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to support the
administration-backed amendment to the foreign aid bill that would
have restored the full $85 million in planned military aid unless a
cease-fre in the civil war there were achieved in 60 days. A ``no''
vote was a vote against the amendment, thus affirming the Senate's
earlier decision to cut the military aid by half.
   Voting ``yes'' were nine Democrats and 30 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 44 Democrats and 14 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
   Adams, D-Wash., no; Akaka, D-Hawaii, no; Armstrong, R-Colo.,
